parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk violently, or hesitate when accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle jerks or lurches when accelerating
the transmission makes abnormal noises
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and jerking can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle jerks or lurches when accelerating
the transmission makes abnormal noises
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Hydraulic Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk violently, or hesitate when accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle jerks or lurches when accelerating
the transmission makes abnormal noises
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power without warning, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds. This can also lead to a loss of control, increasing the risk of crashes or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or accelerates without warning
stalls or loses power
displays "Performance Reduced" or "Engine Service System Urgent" warnings on the dashboard
and may experience intermittent stalling or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. This can also lead to inconvenience, frustration, and financial losses for the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the engine dies completely
the vehicle goes into limp mode
the "Reduced Engine Performance" error message is displayed
the vehicle shakes or vibrates while driving
the cruise control stops working
and the vehicle may not restart immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle runs rough
hesitates
or jerks; loss of power; "Performance Reduced" or similar warning message on the information center; surging or stalling when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause gasoline to spill out of the tank, leading to a fire hazard, environmental damage, and safety risks.
symptoms: Gasoline shoots out of the tank upon completion of filling; emissions warning light is illuminated.
